description.narrative:
The Social Life Project under Karen Development Service Foundation supports Karen ethnic communities on legal status and natural resource management issues with approximate number of 16,764 people in 36 communities in &nbsp;Tha Song Yang district of Tak, Sob Moei district of Mae Hong Son and Wiangpapao of Chiang Rai provinces .The rights holders lack of personal legal status including citizenship causing them difficulties in accessing to other rights such as rights to occupation, educations, health care, politics and that they are vulnerable to various forms of exploitation. Lacking of rights in managing the natural resources and environment, the rights holders encounter conflicts with the duty bearers, they tend to get arrested invading the forest and having difficult livelihood.&nbsp;
The project aims that the target groups access to their rights to citizenships and natural resource management.&nbsp;
The project objectives are improved and solved legal status of the rights holders, collective management of natural resources and the environment in the communities with the government.&nbsp;
The project expects to see increased ability the target groups in dealing with legal status problems, collective cooperation between government sectors and civil society in legal status problem solving, collective participation of the network in advocating for the change of legal status policy, increased awareness and roles of women and youth in natural resources and environment management, available systematic natural resources and environment management such as local ordinances&nbsp; and&nbsp; linkage of networks to high levels for policy advocacy.&nbsp;
Major activities are capacity building, network empowerment, networking, women and youth empowerment.&nbsp;
Focused thematic areas are legal status including citizenship and natural resources management.&nbsp;
Other stakeholders: government sectors such as district office, Forestry office, sub-district administrative office. NGO&rsquo;s such as legal status networks, environmental networks.
